# PM Insights — Cursor Project Rules
# Cursor reads this automatically before every response.

---

## 1. WHAT THIS PROJECT IS

PM Insights is a multi-tenant SaaS that converts App Store and Play Store
reviews into prioritised PM artifacts. A PM pastes their app's Play Store
URL, the system runs a 5-phase AI pipeline, and delivers:
  - Bug Triage Matrix (bugs ranked by severity + frequency)
  - Feature Backlog (ranked by user demand)
  - RICE Prioritisation Table (auto-scored from review volume)
  - Executive Summary (narrative)
  - PRD Draft (new — Claude-generated from a single feature cluster click)

Target user: a Product Manager at a mobile-first company.
They are non-technical. Zero CLI interaction. Everything via web UI.

---

## 2. EXISTING CODE — READ BEFORE TOUCHING ANY FILE

### PRESERVE exactly — do not rewrite logic:
- backend/agent/prompts/ — all prompt files contain carefully engineered
  system prompts. Change NOTHING inside these files this sprint.
- backend/agent/tools/ — extraction, clustering, scoring logic. Wrap only.
- backend/agent/artifacts/ — artifact builders (bug triage, RICE, feature).
- backend/pipeline/ — ingestion, normalization, scraper. Preserve exactly.
- backend/database/schema.sql — reference for column names when building
  the new PostgreSQL schema.

### DEPRECATED — use only as reference for data shapes, not as patterns:
- legacy/ — old Streamlit app and CLI run scripts. Never import from here.
- backend/database/db.py — SQLite-based. Do not use. See Section 10.
- backend/config/settings.py — has hardcoded Spotify defaults and Notion
  config. See Section 10. Migrate to pydantic-settings.

---

## 3. TARGET ARCHITECTURE

### Backend
- Framework: FastAPI (Python 3.11+), async throughout
- Database: PostgreSQL via Supabase (supabase-py client, NOT SQLAlchemy)
- Auth: Supabase Auth — verify JWT in FastAPI middleware
- Queue: Celery + Redis for async pipeline runs
- AI routing: see Section 6
- Config: pydantic-settings (backend/core/config.py), all secrets from .env

### Frontend
- Framework: Next.js 14, App Router only (never Pages Router)
- Styling: Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui components only
- State: Zustand for client state, TanStack Query for server state
- Auth: @supabase/supabase-js
- Forms: React Hook Form + Zod
- HTTP: typed API client in frontend/lib/api.ts

### Infrastructure
- Backend: Railway (FastAPI + Celery worker + Redis)
- Frontend: Vercel
- Storage: Supabase Storage (exported PDFs)

---

## 4. MULTI-TENANCY — CRITICAL

Every database table MUST have `user_id UUID NOT NULL`.
Enable Supabase Row Level Security on every table.
Never write a Supabase query without `.eq('user_id', user.id)`.

Schema hierarchy: users → apps → runs → atoms → clusters → artifacts

---

## 5. CORE DOMAIN MODEL — use these exact names everywhere

```
App       id, user_id, name, play_store_id, app_store_id, category, created_at

Run       id, app_id, user_id, status(pending|processing|complete|failed),
          date_from, date_to, review_count, created_at, completed_at

Atom      id, run_id, review_id, atom_type(bug|feature_request|sentiment|ux_issue),
          text, severity(low|medium|high|critical), product_area,
          confidence_score, source_review

Cluster   id, run_id, label, atom_count, frequency_score, avg_severity,
          product_area, sample_atoms(jsonb)

Artifact  id, run_id, cluster_id(nullable), artifact_type
          (bug_triage_matrix|feature_backlog|rice_table|executive_summary|prd_draft),
          content(jsonb), markdown(text), created_at
```

Use these exact field names in Pydantic models, API responses, TypeScript
types. Do not rename or abbreviate.

---

## 6. AI MODEL ROUTING

| Task                       | Model            | Reason                |
|----------------------------|------------------|-----------------------|
| Atomic extraction          | Gemini 2.5 Flash | Speed + cost at scale |
| Cluster label adjudication | Groq / Llama3    | Sub-second latency    |
| PRD draft generation       | Claude Sonnet    | Quality + structure   |
| Executive summary          | Claude Haiku     | Cost efficiency       |
| Competitor diff summary    | Claude Haiku     | Cost efficiency       |

Never use Claude for atomic extraction.
Never use Gemini for PRD drafts.
Wrap all LLM calls with exponential backoff for rate limits.

---

## 7. PRD GENERATOR — new feature spec

Trigger: user clicks "Generate PRD" on any Cluster card.

Input: cluster.label, cluster.atom_count, cluster.avg_severity,
       cluster.sample_atoms (top 10), cluster.product_area,
       app.name, run.date_from, run.date_to

Claude system prompt (use exactly this in backend/services/ai_service.py):
"""
You are a senior product manager writing a Product Requirements Document.
Write concisely. No filler phrases. Every sentence is a fact, decision, or question.
Output a PRD with exactly these sections using these headers:
## Problem Statement
## User Stories
## Acceptance Criteria
## Out of Scope
## Open Questions
Do not add any other sections. No introduction or conclusion.
"""

Store as Artifact with artifact_type='prd_draft'.

---

## 8. API CONVENTIONS

Base path: /api/v1/
Response envelope:
  { "data": {...}|[...]|null, "error": null|{"code":"","message":""}, "meta": {"request_id":"","timestamp":""} }

Routes:
  POST   /api/v1/apps
  GET    /api/v1/apps
  POST   /api/v1/apps/{app_id}/runs
  GET    /api/v1/apps/{app_id}/runs
  GET    /api/v1/runs/{run_id}/status
  GET    /api/v1/runs/{run_id}/artifacts
  POST   /api/v1/clusters/{cluster_id}/prd

Auth: every route requires `user = Depends(get_current_user)`.

---

## 9. CODE STYLE

Python:
  - async/await everywhere in FastAPI
  - Pydantic v2 (model_config, not class Config)
  - Type hints on all function signatures
  - structlog for logging — never print()
  - Business logic in services/ — never in route handlers
  - Max 40 lines per function

TypeScript:
  - strict: true — no `any`
  - Server Components by default; 'use client' only when needed
  - Tailwind only — no inline styles
  - API calls only through frontend/lib/api.ts

---

## 10. NEVER DO — hard rules

- NEVER use SQLite. PostgreSQL via Supabase only.
- NEVER import or use Notion SDK. Notion is removed.
- NEVER generate CLI scripts (no argparse, no --run_id flags).
- NEVER hardcode app names or app IDs (Spotify is gone).
- NEVER use print() — use structlog.
- NEVER put business logic in route handlers.
- NEVER query a table without user_id filter.
- NEVER use Pages Router in Next.js.
- NEVER rewrite logic in backend/agent/ — wrap it in services.
- NEVER write to an /outputs/ directory at runtime.
- NEVER commit .env files.

---

